The paper discusses privacy-preserving data publishing (PPDP) for trajectory micro-data, which involves protecting the privacy of individuals' spatiotemporal information. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR), as attacks on trajectory micro-data are a major concern. Additionally, the paper discusses solutions proposed for protecting databases, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques for preserving privacy, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the emerging technologies that enable the collection of trajectory micro-data, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
